values: 湖；湖泊；湖水；人造湖；（某地区的）湖群
使血球溶解；诱发溶血现象

word_group.brief_definition: 湖泊水位；湖面水位；湖的水位

bilingual.source: Look at the people on the lake.
We rowed a boat on the lake.
There are many ducks on the lake.
There is a lake near the village.
We went for a long walk around the lake.
bilingual.target: 我们绕着湖走了很长一段路。

bilingual.source: Which is the deepest salt lake in the world?
bilingual.target: 世界上最深的咸水湖是哪一个？

list.abstract: Madina Lake Madina Lake 　　Madina Lake 2005年成立
lake是一个英语单词，名词、动词，作名词时意思是“湖；深红色颜料；胭脂红”，作动词时意思是“（使）血球溶解”。

yingyinNormal.en: Everybody loves boating on the lake.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大家都喜欢在湖上划船！

yingyinNormal.en: It will be really good if it has a lake. Yes, a lake. One lake. But it needs water to be a proper lake. Oh.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果有湖就好了。是的，一个湖。一个湖。但是真正的湖需要有水。哦！

yingyinNormal.en: You have come from Lake-town.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是从长湖城来的。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, not so much the Lake of Wisdom, it's more like the Lake of Whiz.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，与其说是智慧之湖，看来叫做污秽之湖更合适。

yingyinNormal.en: No one enters Lake-town but by lead of the master.
yingyinNormal.zh: 除非城主带路，没有人进得了长湖城。

yingyinNormal.en: This isn't their fault. Wait, you cannot go to Lake-town!
yingyinNormal.zh: 这和他们无关，别去长湖城。

yingyinNormal.en: Excuse me, but, you're from Lake-town, if I'm not mistaken?
yingyinNormal.zh: 不好意思，你是从长湖城来的，我没看错吧？

yingyinNormal.en: We could go up to Big Bear and get a house on the lake. Did you see The Lake House?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们可以去大熊湖找一间湖边小屋。你们没看过《湖边小屋》吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Hello, Pedro. We've got a desert island, with houses. And roads. Shops. Trees. And a lake. But we need water for the lake. Have you got some, please?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好，佩德罗。我们有一个有房子的荒岛。还有路，商店，树和一个湖。但是我们需要为湖找水，你有吗？

yingyinNormal.en: And just beyond the lake, there was a prison. This isn't scary.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在湖那边，有一个监狱。一点都不吓人啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, three days on the lake without a shower. Plus. I fell in that big tub of worms at the bait stand.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我在湖上3天没洗澡 ，还掉进一桶鱼饵里。

yingyinNormal.en: Riding in the pedalo on a sunny lake. Daddy is the engine, I hope he doesn't break.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在洒满阳光的湖上划着船，爸爸是发动机，我希望他不会坏掉。

yingyinNormal.en: Daddy, can we have some water in our bucket, please? We're making a lake. Of course.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪爸爸，我们能用桶取一些水吗？我们正在造一个湖。哦！当然。

yingyinNormal.en: We go out on the lake almost every weekend. Or, we did, till I moved away.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们几乎每周末都去湖上滑冰，应该说，我们以前都去，直到...搬来这里。

yingyinNormal.en: Who's the one who brought you to the car? Who's the one who found the lake and brought you to the car?
yingyinNormal.zh: 谁帮你找到了沉车？谁发现了那片湖然后带你找到了沉车？

yingyinNormal.en: I remember, when I was a kid, me and my father, we went ice fishing out on Lake Wissota. Ice fishing is, you know, where you...
yingyinNormal.zh: 我小时候跟父亲到威苏塔湖，在冰上钓鱼，冰上钓鱼就是…

yingyinNormal.en: Middle school. A clear lake of untroubled spring water. High school is a bathroom full of these train wrecks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 初中就是一湖无烦恼的清澈泉水，高中则是充满车祸现场的洗手间。

yingyinNormal.en: Where? Near Barbosa Lake. He was standing on the edge of a ravine. What did Robert tell you when you got there?
yingyinNormal.zh: 在哪？在巴博萨湖附近。他站在峡谷边上。你到之后罗伯特跟你说了什么？

yingyinNormal.en: Sometimes, these confessions are hoaxes but based on his story, we were able to return to the lake site where we discovered trace DNA matching that of Mr. Cartoff in critical areas of the search zone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有时候，这些认罪行为是恶作剧但是根据他的描述，我们回到我们发现微量DNA的湖的位置，这些DNA被证实与卡托夫先生的相吻合，同时这个湖是在搜寻区的关键位置。

yingyinNormal.en: One afternoon, off the coast of Lake Superior, he spotted a yacht in peril. He rowed out and rescued the vessel and its captain, alcoholic millionaire Dan Cody.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一天下午，在苏必利尔湖的岸边，他看见一艘游艇处于险境，他奋力划行，拯救了那游艇和它的主人酒鬼富豪，丹·科迪。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: British land artists preferred to get away from towns, gravitating towards landscapes that are traditionally considered beautiful such as the <highlight>Lake</highlight> District.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英国地景艺术家更喜欢远离城镇，被传统上被认为美丽的风景所吸引，比如英国湖区。

word_usage.usage: 英美国家的湖泊名称，常把专有名词后置，且不加冠词，如：Lake Ontario（安大略湖）；而中国的湖泊名称，常把专有名词前置，且加定冠词，如：the West lake（西湖）。

examination_example.sentence: One doesn't need to travel long hours anymore or go to other <highlight>lakes</highlight> to watch the birds.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 许多鸟类已经迁徙到这个地区，人们不再需要长途跋涉或去其他湖泊观看鸟类。

examination_example.sentence: The land has been connected to the network of <highlight>lakes</highlight> and streams in the area.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这片陆地与该地区的湖泊和溪流相连。

examination_example.sentence: Then I met Bob at the <highlight>lake</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然后我在湖边遇见了鲍勃。

examination_example.sentence: We could probably just walk by the <highlight>lake</highlight>, and I'll ask Mike to join us.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们也许可以在湖边散步，我会邀请Mike和我们一起去。

examination_example.sentence: Her popular 1962 book Silent Spring raised awareness of the harmful effects of chemicals on humans and on the world's <highlight>lakes</highlight> and oceans.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她在1962年出版的畅销书《寂静的春天》，提高了人们的认识——化学品对人类和世界湖泊和海洋的有害影响。

examination_example.sentence: People and factories are polluting the air, rivers, <highlight>lakes</highlight> and seas.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人类和工厂正在污染空气、河流、湖泊和海洋。

examination_example.sentence: I'm looking forward to seeing the colourful <highlight>lakes</highlight> and amazing waterfalls．
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我期待看到五颜六色的湖泊和令人惊叹的瀑布。

examination_example.sentence: Jack caught more big fish, and put them all back into the <highlight>lake</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Jack抓到了更多大鱼，并把它们都放回了湖里。
